<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>THE TRADE AND KEEPING OF NON-HUMAN PRIMATES AS PETS</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">WRITTEN EVIDENCE SUBMITTED TO THE EFRA COMMITTEE ON BEHALF OF THE GLOBAL FEDERATION OF ANIMAL SANCTUARIES</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> (GFAS)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">January 2014</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">he EFRA Committee is seeking written submissions of evidence in regard to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the following:</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The extent of the trade and keeping of primates as pets within the UK;</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Whether the existing regulatory framework and Code of Practice offer adequate protection for the welfare of primates kept as pets</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and are being applied effectively; and</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Whether people should be allowed to keep primates as pets and, if not, how a ban might be implemented.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The following is submitted on behalf of the Global Federation of Animal Sanctuaries (GFAS).</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">SUMMARY</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">GFAS serves to promote </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">optimum</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> standards of operation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">al management and animal care in animal sanctuaries worldwide.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">GFAS is concerned about the number </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and range </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">of primates kept in the UK</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">are convinced</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> that it is not possible to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> adequately</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> meet the needs of primates when being kept as pet</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">GFAS is conce</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">rned about</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the apparent </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">lack of rehoming facilities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> for primates kept as pets</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.03pt; padding-left:7.97pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">W</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">e fully support a ban on the keeping and trade of primates as pets.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">1, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">About GFAS</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Global Federation of Animal Sanctuaries (GFAS) is an international non-profit organisati</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">on dedicated to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">helping sanctuaries to help animals.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">GFAS promotes and validates excellence in sanctuary management and humane and responsible care of animals through a global system of accreditation, collaboration and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">mentoring. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> GFAS promotes the develop</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ment of greater recognition and r</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">esources for sanctuaries, and works</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">eliminate the causes of displaced animals.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">GFAS is proud to provide </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">comprehensive</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> standards on sanctuary excellence,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and operates a </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">rigorous accreditation system </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">by which sanctuaries are assessed against these standards </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">through a written application, review of documents and site visit, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in order to achieve</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> accreditation and verification. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The GFAS Standards of Excellence were developed and reviewed with the input of</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> animal </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">welfare experts</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, non-profit professionals, sanctuary managers, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and veterinarians, utilis</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ing existing standards from outstanding sanctuaries as a starting framework and refined/expanded upon based on knowledge and expertise of contributors.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">GFAS con</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">siders a </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">sanctuary </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">to be </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">an establishment that provides lifetime care for animals that have been abused, injured, abandoned, or are otherwise in need. The animals may come from sources </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">including, but not limited to, private owners, research laboratories, g</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">overnment authorities, the entertainment industry, and zoos.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">All GFAS </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">sanctuaries</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> must adhere to certain policies as set out in our standards, including but not limited to:</span></p><ul type="square" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 27.58pt; padding-left:8.42pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">no commercial trade in animals or animal parts;</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 27.58pt; padding-left:8.42pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">no animals removed from enclosures </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">for exhibition;</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 27.58pt; padding-left:8.42pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">no direct contact</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> between the public and animals;</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 27.58pt; padding-left:8.42pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">humane </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">measures in place to prevent breeding, unless the animals are part of a bona fide release program;</span></li><li style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 27.58pt; padding-left:8.42pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">open</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to the public only by way of a structured visitor program in which tours are guided and where there is a bona fide educational component to the visiting program.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Facilities that are not genuine </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">sanctuaries, on the other hand, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">may </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">buy and sell </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">primates</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, ex</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">hibit the animals on and off site, allow the public to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">have direct contact with primates</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, breed </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">primates</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, and allow the public </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">to visit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> on a regular basis without escort. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In addition, their </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">facilities </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">may be substandard. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Situation in the UK</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">GFAS has ac</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">credited and verified several primate sanctuaries in North America, where the issue of primates as pets is a particular problem in terms of numbers. </span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">To date, GFAS has accredited one primate sanctuary in the UK. We are aware of a handful of other primate-ke</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">eping facilities across Europe that might also meet the standards for verification or accreditation by GFAS.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">It is apparent that there is a dearth of suitable facilities for rehoming and rescuing primates. Allowing the ownership and trade of pet primates t</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">o continue without this safety net would be irresponsible.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We note that there is currently no definition of an animal sanctuary in UK legislation. We do not consider that this should be an obstacle to a ban on the keeping of primates as pets. Genuine sanc</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">tuaries do not keep primates as pets, nor do they keep them specifically for exhibition. Furthermore they do not trade in primates.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> A ban on the keeping of pet primates or on the trade in primates would be unlikely to affect the activities of responsible a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">nimal sanctuaries, particularly if legislation is tailored towards </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">banning </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the keeping of primates by individuals in a domestic environment.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">3. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Conclusions</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">are convinced </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">that the keeping of primates in the UK should be restricted to licensed zoos and to genuine animal sanctuaries. We consider facilities </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">to be genuine sanctuaries if they </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">are already accredited or verified by GFAS, or are likely to comply with GFAS standards</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">At this time, we do not offer comment on whether a ban on the keeping and/or a ban on the trade in primates as pets is the most suitable mechanism for achieving this restriction.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In the event of a ban, GFAS remains willing to assist Defra and other stake</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">holders in advising on the best options for primates currently kept as pets.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">GFAS looks forward to working with and alongside other stakeholders in verifying and/or accrediting suitable facilities across Europe, where appropriate.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Prepared for GFAS by Chr</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">is Draper, GFAS Europe representative</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>